      "span_text": "Previous investigations utilizing defective interfering RNAs have confirmed that no more than the first 604 nt of the 5= UTR and the entirety of the 3= UTR are sufficient to allow both positive-and negative-strand RNA synthesis; it is notable that this region only includes one-third of the U1 ORF (which starts at nucleotide 524), hence only this subdomain would be constrained by maintaining two distinct functional roles."
